						               													<description>How To Play&amp;#10;Shuffle the deck and deal each player a hand of 11 cards. Set the remaining cards aside.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each trick (or turn) of the game consists of every player placing 1 card into the middle of the playing surface, in clockwise order.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player to the dealer's left begins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For each trick, the first card played must be one of the game's 8 suits&amp;ndash; cat, zombie, werewolf, witch, vampire, ghost, monster or mummy. Subsequent cards played in a trick must follow suit, unless a player does not have a card of said suit, or holds a special (!) card (which may be played instead). The player with the highest value card played, of the dominant suit, takes the trick. Players score 1 point for every card of any type taken, as well as bonus/penalty points listed on special cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The trick taker begins the next turn. Special cards cannot be used to start a trick. If the player starting a trick has only special cards to play, all remaining tricks of the hand are void, along with that player being assessed a -15 point penalty.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to 100 points, wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
